Yesterday I was telling the guests at this event how honored I always am to speak at these types of engagements. A lot of women AND men instantly judge and turn their nose up at me because they’ve seen me on reality tv. So I definitely developed that “imposter syndrome”. Constantly feeling like I didn’t belong in rooms with certain people, or asking myself “who’s going to want to learn anything from me”? 

Before I ever got on a reality tv show I was a college graduate working in professional settings while driving to Hollywood on my lunch breaks for auditions. Basically … I put in hella work and accomplished a lot before anyone ever knew my name or seen my face. So my message was simply … IT’S NOT YOUR BUSINESS WHAT ANYONE THINKS OF YOU 💅🏾

Thank God for this year. I’ve learned so much about myself and my purpose. Thank every single person who has supported me by buying these books and journals.
